1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,960
Rituals, beliefs, and myths in this series are a work of fiction and in no regard refer to religions or faiths of any certain cultures.

2
00:00:12,720 --> 00:00:16,320
Fate is woven by three forces.

3
00:00:16,560 --> 00:00:20,520
However, the fate of some is made to be
more complicated than that.

4
00:00:20,680 --> 00:00:23,120
Does heaven still
allow me to do this or not?

5
00:00:23,120 --> 00:00:26,000
Everything that’s happened
is the work of an evil force,

6
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:27,040
not the will of heaven.

7
00:00:27,120 --> 00:00:29,960
The Six-Eared Macaque’s power is to hear everything between heaven and earth.

8
00:00:29,960 --> 00:00:32,800
You have to borrow its power
to locate Qi Rong.

9
00:00:33,520 --> 00:00:36,600
You have to do whatever it takes
not to let the demon devour you.

10
00:00:52,160 --> 00:00:54,240
15.17.

11
00:00:55,280 --> 00:00:56,480
The demon appears.

12
00:00:57,520 --> 00:00:59,600
- Shit!
- Crap!

13
00:01:06,880 --> 00:01:07,360
Pete.

14
00:01:07,680 --> 00:01:08,560
Can you hear me?

15
00:01:17,520 --> 00:01:19,640
Take that, you jerk!

16
00:01:26,440 --> 00:01:28,120
How else to extinguish fire?

17
00:01:48,880 --> 00:01:49,720
Where’s everyone?

18
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:51,440
They all went home.

19
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:53,479
You were out cold for five hours.

20
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:57,880
Five hours…

21
00:02:05,240 --> 00:02:06,280
(Pete! Pete!)

22
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:10,000
The Six-Eared Macaque inside you
is more powerful than I expected.

23
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:13,720
It likely has taken control of you before.

24
00:02:17,880 --> 00:02:19,640
How come I don’t remember anything?

25
00:02:23,920 --> 00:02:25,440
And that happened before, didn’t it?

26
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:29,200
What do you mean?

27
00:02:30,240 --> 00:02:32,960
There must be moments where you
feel like you don’t remember happening.

28
00:02:37,880 --> 00:02:38,480
Fuck!

29
00:02:41,560 --> 00:02:42,400
There were.

30
00:02:42,840 --> 00:02:47,760
Fei and Jia Hao said it’s too risky
to use you in this ritual.

31
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:49,840
They told me to find another way.

32
00:02:50,840 --> 00:02:52,480
But I don’t think we have any options.

33
00:02:54,079 --> 00:02:55,120
What does that mean?

34
00:02:55,920 --> 00:02:59,760
It means I have to find a way for you to gain control over the monkey inside you.

35
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:35,080
NIRAN

36
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:41,440
Yo?

37
00:04:43,400 --> 00:04:44,040
What?

38
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:51,840
What the hell are you doing here
first thing in the morning?

39
00:04:51,960 --> 00:04:52,960
I’m moving in.

40
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:53,680
What?

41
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:55,240
Hey!

42
00:04:56,520 --> 00:04:57,120
Wait!

43
00:04:58,200 --> 00:05:02,000
Did you forget I have to train you
to use the demon’s power?

44
00:05:02,360 --> 00:05:04,080
It’s more convenient if I just live here.

45
00:05:04,640 --> 00:05:05,240
Hold on.

46
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:09,400
You’re moving in, but you didn’t
even think to ask me first?

47
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:10,200
Why should I?

48
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:11,560
This is my house now.

49
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:13,600
I bought it from your relative.

50
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:18,400
What?

51
00:05:19,440 --> 00:05:20,800
That jerk-ass of an uncle.

52
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:24,000
I gave him a million as a deposit!

53
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:27,920
For a 10 million-baht house,
a million-baht deposit doesn’t mean jack.

54
00:05:28,320 --> 00:05:29,760
Damn it.

55
00:05:31,960 --> 00:05:33,640
Uncle, how could you do this?

56
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,480
What about that one million I gave you?

57
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,200
What the hell, Uncle?

58
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:38,520
Come on!

59
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:40,400
You can’t do this!

60
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:49,920
Damn it.

61
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:51,280
My uncle is useless.

62
00:05:53,080 --> 00:05:53,440
Well?

63
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:55,560
Is he gonna give you back the deposit?

64
00:05:55,640 --> 00:05:56,720
I don’t give a shit.

65
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:58,320
He said he’s gonna give it back
to me tomorrow.

66
00:05:58,320 --> 00:05:59,480
But it’s not the money I want.

67
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:00,880
I want my house back.

68
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:02,120
Is that so?

69
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:05,280
I guess you’ll have to buy it from me.

70
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:06,720
I’m selling it for 30 million, though.

71
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:07,440
Oh, you fuc—

72
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:08,280
Hold on.

73
00:06:08,960 --> 00:06:10,040
50 million.

74
00:06:10,440 --> 00:06:11,320
After we’re done with this job,

75
00:06:11,480 --> 00:06:15,560
you can buy this house back with
the money you told me to split with you.

76
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:16,640
Isn’t that nice?

77
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:17,520
Jerk.

78
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:18,560
This ain’t funny.

79
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:19,440
It’s my damn house.

80
00:06:19,520 --> 00:06:20,320
That’s too bad.

81
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:23,000
The deed says otherwise.

82
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:29,800
This room’s perfect.

83
00:06:30,240 --> 00:06:30,960
I’ll take it.

84
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:33,400
Get your stuff out.

85
00:06:34,280 --> 00:06:35,040
Damn.

86
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:37,720
You’re hellbent on messing
with me today, huh?

87
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:41,000
Do I need to remind you
we’re going to seal a demon soon?

88
00:06:41,240 --> 00:06:43,840
I am the fashi of the ritual.

89
00:06:43,840 --> 00:06:44,520
So?

90
00:06:44,840 --> 00:06:45,680
So, you jerk…

91
00:06:46,520 --> 00:06:48,200
I have to be in tip-top condition,

92
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:50,200
otherwise you and everyone else
will be in trouble.

93
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:54,000
I have to sleep somewhere
with good energy flow.

94
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:55,560
Hey.

95
00:07:00,640 --> 00:07:01,200
Hey!

96
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:02,520
Just pick another room!

97
00:07:02,520 --> 00:07:03,600
There is more than enough room here!

98
00:07:03,640 --> 00:07:04,600
I want this one.

99
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:05,440
But I live here!

100
00:07:05,520 --> 00:07:06,760
Go away!

101
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:08,200
This is my room!

102
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:09,320
Don’t you get what I said, Pete?

103
00:07:09,320 --> 00:07:09,720
No!

104
00:07:09,960 --> 00:07:10,400
Go away!

105
00:07:10,880 --> 00:07:12,440
You want to put everyone’s lives at risk?

106
00:07:12,440 --> 00:07:13,800
I ain’t risking no one’s lives.

107
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:15,240
There are other rooms for you!

108
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:17,360
And I told you this room
has the best energy flow!

109
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:19,120
Pete!

110
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:25,560
You happy now?

111
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:27,880
Yeah.

112
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:31,240
Now we can start training.

113
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:36,320
What do I have to do?

114
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:44,760
I said stay still.

115
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:46,920
You asshole.

116
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:51,560
Can you at least tell me
why I’m doing this?

117
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:56,520
To use the demon’s power,
first, you have to get stronger.

118
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:58,240
Hey!

119
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:07,040
From now on, you get up
when the sun comes up.

120
00:08:10,000 --> 00:08:11,280
Ugh!

121
00:08:16,320 --> 00:08:16,920
Slower.

122
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:17,560
What?

123
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,120
You need to run more slowly.

124
00:08:19,440 --> 00:08:21,120
Any slower than this,
I might as well be walking.

125
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:23,080
Breathe into your stomach.

126
00:08:25,520 --> 00:08:27,120
That jerk…

127
00:08:31,440 --> 00:08:32,480
Don’t smoke inside.

128
00:08:34,640 --> 00:08:37,200
And you’re not allowed to smoke
more than five cigarettes a day now.

129
00:08:45,280 --> 00:08:47,040
Do I have to carry this crap?

130
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:49,280
You need to learn how to run slowly.

131
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:50,680
Keep going.

132
00:08:50,920 --> 00:08:51,240
Hurry up.

133
00:09:12,400 --> 00:09:13,640
What the hell are you doing?

134
00:09:14,280 --> 00:09:15,080
You up, jerk?

135
00:09:28,040 --> 00:09:28,640
Get back up.

136
00:09:32,280 --> 00:09:32,720
Stay still.

137
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:34,360
Focus.

138
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:35,920
Stay still.

139
00:09:44,560 --> 00:09:45,760
You fool, I told you to stay still.

140
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:47,440
Hey!

141
00:09:48,640 --> 00:09:49,120
Ugh!

142
00:09:49,240 --> 00:09:50,000
Focus.

143
00:09:50,040 --> 00:09:51,600
What more do you want from me?

144
00:09:58,800 --> 00:10:00,680
Oh, crap! What the hell, man?

145
00:10:00,680 --> 00:10:01,720
That was rough.

146
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:02,640
Jack, help me out, man.

147
00:10:17,240 --> 00:10:19,000
Thua, what the hell are you doing?

148
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:20,560
Hey!

149
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:25,720
What the hell do you think
you’re doing, Pete?

150
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:27,080
Why aren’t you training?

151
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:30,040
I’ve been training all week.

152
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:31,240
I need a break.

153
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:32,640
You do?

154
00:10:33,560 --> 00:10:36,560
You think you can just take a break
whenever you want?

155
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:39,280
I don’t know what you’re
making me do all that for.

156
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:40,880
I don’t know what I’m training for!

157
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:43,440
I’m an athlete.

158
00:10:44,400 --> 00:10:45,920
You think I’m not strong enough?

159
00:10:46,920 --> 00:10:47,840
You’re not an athlete.

160
00:10:50,640 --> 00:10:52,040
You know damn well why
you’re no longer an athlete.

161
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:54,200
How long have you been living like this?

162
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:03,880
All these years you’ve been
wasting your damn breaths,

163
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:08,320
don’t you notice at all
how hollow you are inside?

164
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:10,280
There’s not an ounce
of substance in there!

165
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:14,640
I’ll tell you what.

166
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:18,520
If you keep living like this,

167
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:20,520
you…

168
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:24,600
You will become nothing
more than a vessel,

169
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:27,800
waiting for the demon to devour you.

170
00:11:49,360 --> 00:11:49,960
(Pete!)

171
00:11:50,840 --> 00:11:52,000
(Where the hell were you yesterday?)

172
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:53,000
Why did you skip training?

173
00:11:53,960 --> 00:11:54,680
Answer me!

174
00:11:56,440 --> 00:11:59,920
(Don’t you realize what kind of
expectations your parents had for you?)

175
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:03,360
(Thank God they’re dead, then.)

176
00:12:04,760 --> 00:12:06,200
(Otherwise, they'd have been
so damn disappointed in you.)

177
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:06,840
Fuck you!

178
00:12:09,560 --> 00:12:10,800
(Shit! Shit!)

179
00:12:11,520 --> 00:12:12,400
You asshole!

180
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:16,240
Pete!

181
00:12:18,480 --> 00:12:19,400
Let go of me!

182
00:12:22,040 --> 00:12:23,120
You jerk!

183
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:28,240
When I was 15,

184
00:13:32,040 --> 00:13:33,680
I got into a tournament in Korea.

185
00:13:37,360 --> 00:13:39,240
I went two days ahead.

186
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:44,960
My parents flew there later
to cheer me on.

187
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:53,800
My sister was supposed to come, too,

188
00:13:58,640 --> 00:14:00,400
but she got sick before she could go.

189
00:14:16,760 --> 00:14:18,720
Was it my fault?

190
00:15:24,640 --> 00:15:30,440
(Strength isn’t about how hard
you punch or how fast you run.)

191
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:35,520
(If your root is weak, so is your life force.)

192
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:48,720
(You need to find balance in
your body, energy, and mind.)

193
00:16:13,760 --> 00:16:18,640
(In the end, vitality isn’t a miracle
that happens overnight.)

194
00:16:19,640 --> 00:16:24,120
(It’s built from every little thing
you do every day.)

195
00:16:30,440 --> 00:16:31,600
Ugh!

196
00:16:34,160 --> 00:16:35,960
This place’s even more dusty
than my grandma’s house!

197
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:58,200
MR. CHAISAK KRAIADIREK
PRIME MINISTER

198
00:16:59,280 --> 00:16:59,840
Hello.

199
00:17:00,120 --> 00:17:01,080
(Yo, brother.)

200
00:17:02,040 --> 00:17:03,600
It’s been a while since we last talked.

201
00:17:04,040 --> 00:17:04,800
You good?

202
00:17:05,920 --> 00:17:09,119
You and I have things we need to do.

203
00:17:10,079 --> 00:17:10,720
(You’re right.)

204
00:17:11,119 --> 00:17:12,359
(You said it well.)

205
00:17:13,079 --> 00:17:16,760
Heaven has given us different roles.

206
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:21,560
Then why don’t we leave
each other alone?

207
00:17:24,359 --> 00:17:25,480
What do you want?

208
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,680
Bro, take it easy.

209
00:17:30,560 --> 00:17:33,040
I’m just worried about you.

210
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:37,440
Your situation right now
isn’t looking so good.

211
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:40,800
You’re in power, but you’re not in control.

212
00:17:40,800 --> 00:17:43,320
How can you call yourself a leader?

213
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:45,160
So it’s your doing.

214
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:46,240
Me?

215
00:17:48,120 --> 00:17:49,760
Alright, let’s just say this.

216
00:17:51,440 --> 00:17:54,200
You leave me alone
and I’ll stop.

217
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:54,880
Okay?

218
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:58,720
Politics is all about negotiations,

219
00:17:58,720 --> 00:17:59,280
after all, isn’t it?

220
00:17:59,760 --> 00:18:00,280
That’s right.

221
00:18:02,840 --> 00:18:04,400
(But this is no politics.)

222
00:18:05,640 --> 00:18:07,600
You broke the law.

223
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:12,480
(In this country, no one is above the law.)

224
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:14,800
Not you, or even me.

225
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:17,280
Is that how you want to do this?

226
00:18:17,280 --> 00:18:18,320
Fine!

227
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:20,600
(I’ll drag you to hell!)

228
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:25,320
Contact the Ministry of Interior.

229
00:18:25,320 --> 00:18:26,760
We’ll prioritize his denaturalization.

230
00:18:27,240 --> 00:18:28,280
But…

231
00:18:28,560 --> 00:18:30,280
Our enemy is out in the open now.

232
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:34,720
If we get too aggressive in our approach,
it will only provoke him to attack us, sir.

233
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:36,800
That is why we must strike first.

234
00:18:41,680 --> 00:18:43,040
What a loser!

235
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:50,640
Damn it!

236
00:18:53,120 --> 00:18:53,960
Master…

237
00:18:55,080 --> 00:18:57,920
If the Prime Minister
refused to negotiate with you,

238
00:18:58,320 --> 00:19:01,520
it must mean he has struck
a deal with your country

239
00:19:01,520 --> 00:19:03,240
to send you back.

240
00:19:03,920 --> 00:19:05,400
Chaisak! That weak duke!

241
00:19:06,040 --> 00:19:07,160
He’s too weak to run the country.

242
00:19:07,320 --> 00:19:09,000
Is that why he has to cozy up
to the emperor?

243
00:19:13,160 --> 00:19:13,680
Li Puo.

244
00:19:14,440 --> 00:19:16,800
You said that demon of yours
would help me!

245
00:19:17,520 --> 00:19:19,160
Please, Master.

246
00:19:19,360 --> 00:19:21,440
You must not offend Lord Warrior.

247
00:19:28,600 --> 00:19:30,200
I don’t see how he’s helping me!

248
00:19:40,720 --> 00:19:41,640
Master.

249
00:19:42,120 --> 00:19:46,160
All we need to do is
make Lord Warrior stronger.

250
00:19:46,320 --> 00:19:49,000
Give him more life spirits.

251
00:19:49,080 --> 00:19:52,560
I am sure the situation will grow
to be even more violent, Master.

252
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:56,240
What the hell are you waiting for, then?

253
00:19:57,760 --> 00:19:58,360
Yes, sir.

254
00:19:58,360 --> 00:19:58,840
Go!

255
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:18,320
Holy shit.

256
00:20:20,240 --> 00:20:21,240
Are we even allowed to drink?

257
00:20:21,240 --> 00:20:22,640
Of course.

258
00:20:22,760 --> 00:20:23,640
We’re not monks.

259
00:20:23,840 --> 00:20:24,520
You don’t want to?

260
00:20:24,520 --> 00:20:24,960
I do!

261
00:20:27,080 --> 00:20:27,680
Cheers.

262
00:20:30,400 --> 00:20:30,960
Cheers.

263
00:20:39,120 --> 00:20:40,360
Does this really make you so happy?

264
00:20:40,920 --> 00:20:42,680
It’s so damn good.

265
00:20:50,040 --> 00:20:53,480
You must have trained just as hard
in order to become Wu.

266
00:20:55,360 --> 00:20:56,000
Not really.

267
00:20:56,480 --> 00:21:01,560
You’re training to strengthen your life force
which will suppress the demon within you.

268
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:04,600
But my training wasn’t anything like that.

269
00:21:05,440 --> 00:21:07,680
We don’t train to gain strength.

270
00:21:08,120 --> 00:21:11,320
We train to connect with nature
and borrow its power.

271
00:21:12,680 --> 00:21:13,360
Damn.

272
00:21:13,640 --> 00:21:14,440
How do you do that?

273
00:21:17,880 --> 00:21:21,360
If it was something I can share,
everyone on earth would easily be Wu.

274
00:21:21,720 --> 00:21:22,120
Oh.

275
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:26,840
Let’s just say it’s passed down by blood.

276
00:21:27,920 --> 00:21:30,680
There’s no way you can become one
unless we have the same ancestors.

277
00:21:30,840 --> 00:21:33,080
Well, you never know.

278
00:21:33,280 --> 00:21:37,920
Maybe our great-great-great-great-great grandfathers had the same surname.

279
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:41,280
What a dork.

280
00:21:57,960 --> 00:21:58,960
Thank you.

281
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:07,880
For not giving up on me.

282
00:22:25,680 --> 00:22:31,160
I’m not surprised one bit why Fei
comes to you when she needs help.

283
00:22:32,240 --> 00:22:35,920
I’m also not surprised
why Jia Hao agreed to help you.

284
00:22:38,600 --> 00:22:39,320
Well…

285
00:22:40,600 --> 00:22:42,840
I guess they think
I’m one of them outcasts.

286
00:22:43,840 --> 00:22:44,480
Oh, you jerk.

287
00:22:44,920 --> 00:22:47,680
I think they just want
to have you in their lives.

288
00:22:50,680 --> 00:22:52,920
You run away from them, don’t you?

289
00:22:53,520 --> 00:22:55,760
And you isolate yourself, am I right?

290
00:23:03,760 --> 00:23:04,440
Niran.

291
00:23:05,480 --> 00:23:10,880
You need to realize how at ease
you make people feel

292
00:23:13,480 --> 00:23:16,360
…when you’re around.

293
00:23:20,120 --> 00:23:24,960
I just can’t work out why you would be
thought of as an ‘outcast.’

294
00:23:25,520 --> 00:23:28,000
It just makes no damn sense.

295
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:38,920
Almost 10 years ago,
there was this one yao.

296
00:23:40,280 --> 00:23:42,120
It was very powerful.

297
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:45,800
So powerful it could cause a blackout
all through a whole industrial district.

298
00:23:50,320 --> 00:23:56,240
The elders Wu thought it was dangerous,
a threat to the nation.

299
00:23:57,120 --> 00:23:58,560
They sent me to defeat it.

300
00:24:02,680 --> 00:24:05,520
But that yao was born from the despair
of the workers in that district

301
00:24:06,120 --> 00:24:08,160
who were exploited by
their employers for decades.

302
00:24:09,400 --> 00:24:10,480
Now I was wondering…

303
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:13,560
If I defeat it, what’s next?

304
00:24:14,920 --> 00:24:16,480
The factories would be back to business,

305
00:24:17,320 --> 00:24:19,280
and the workers continue to be exploited?

306
00:24:21,240 --> 00:24:22,360
Once they saw that

307
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:26,760
I was asking questions,
they sent Sira to defeat it instead.

308
00:24:30,560 --> 00:24:32,800
That was the first time.

309
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:36,440
But…

310
00:24:38,560 --> 00:24:42,000
I guess there were
more moments like that

311
00:24:43,120 --> 00:24:46,320
where I acted in a way that made them
realize how much I don’t belong.

312
00:24:52,440 --> 00:24:54,000
I’ll admit I think about it sometimes.

313
00:24:55,320 --> 00:25:02,360
If I had just followed orders,
maybe I wouldn’t be where I am right now.

314
00:25:03,080 --> 00:25:09,560
I probably wouldn’t be an outcast.

315
00:25:12,280 --> 00:25:13,200
And…

316
00:25:14,800 --> 00:25:18,280
Maybe I’d even get a chance
to be Wu properly like I should.

317
00:25:27,240 --> 00:25:28,120
Niran.

318
00:25:29,960 --> 00:25:31,240
Listen to me.

319
00:25:32,280 --> 00:25:34,040
I don’t know what you were like in the past.

320
00:25:34,440 --> 00:25:39,320
But I want you to know
that you’re not alone now.

321
00:25:41,280 --> 00:25:46,680
You have people who accept you,
and are willing to stick by you.

322
00:25:50,960 --> 00:25:53,680
You just need to let them.

323
00:26:03,520 --> 00:26:03,880
Cheers?

324
00:26:06,640 --> 00:26:07,240
Cheers.

325
00:26:19,120 --> 00:26:19,680
Damn.

326
00:26:20,280 --> 00:26:23,360
No matter how shitty the world is,
beer is always pretty damn amazing.

327
00:26:23,760 --> 00:26:26,320
Bottoms up, dude. Let’s have a duel.

328
00:26:37,160 --> 00:26:37,760
Ploy.

329
00:26:38,080 --> 00:26:39,120
STUDENT ASSOCIATION
AGAINST VIOLENCE

330
00:26:39,120 --> 00:26:41,880
(The demonstrations are still ongoing,)

331
00:26:41,880 --> 00:26:47,400
(after the Prime Minister refused to resign despite the protesters’ demands,)

332
00:26:47,400 --> 00:26:51,880
(and promised to arrest anyone
breaking the laws.)

333
00:26:52,360 --> 00:26:54,280
(However, there has been a movement)

334
00:26:54,280 --> 00:26:57,440
(from the Student Association
for Democracy,)

335
00:26:57,520 --> 00:27:01,440
(condemning the current violence.)

336
00:27:01,560 --> 00:27:05,400
(They are calling for
a peaceful negotiation.)

337
00:27:05,440 --> 00:27:08,600
(The students will gather to cite
their litany of complaints tomorrow.)

338
00:27:08,720 --> 00:27:11,720
(Hello, people and people of the press.)

339
00:27:11,880 --> 00:27:14,880
(We are the Student Association
for Democracy.)

340
00:27:15,080 --> 00:27:18,560
(We stand by our stances towards the current political climate, as follows:)

341
00:27:18,640 --> 00:27:22,400
(First, we do not condone
violence from both parties.)

342
00:27:22,840 --> 00:27:27,600
(Second, we directly address the leaders
of our nation to handle this issue )

343
00:27:27,800 --> 00:27:29,080
(according to the principles of democracy
in a peaceful manner.)

344
00:27:29,480 --> 00:27:30,920
It’s just a gathering on campus.

345
00:27:32,080 --> 00:27:33,400
There’s probably nothing to worry about.

346
00:27:40,480 --> 00:27:42,640
Not long now, Lord Warrior.

347
00:27:43,520 --> 00:27:46,040
I have found you a sacrifice.

348
00:27:59,800 --> 00:28:00,720
Listen up.

349
00:28:01,800 --> 00:28:06,040
Our country has been experiencing political turmoil for more than 20 years.

350
00:28:06,400 --> 00:28:09,760
It has hurt and weakened us
for far too long.

351
00:28:09,760 --> 00:28:10,840
DISSOLVE PARLIAMENT.

352
00:28:10,840 --> 00:28:11,360
RESIGN. POWER BACK TO PEOPLE

353
00:28:11,360 --> 00:28:15,880
It is our duty to make
our democracy stronger.

354
00:28:16,720 --> 00:28:18,360
We say no to street politics.

355
00:28:18,520 --> 00:28:20,160
We say no to a coup d'etat!

356
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:27,120
- Say no!
- Say no!

357
00:28:27,120 --> 00:28:29,080
THE HOUSE IS ALL
CLEANED UP NOW, PLOY

358
00:28:35,320 --> 00:28:35,880
Ploy!

359
00:28:37,880 --> 00:28:38,840
You’re up.

360
00:29:04,560 --> 00:29:09,040
In this situation,
we must demand of both parties:

361
00:29:09,560 --> 00:29:10,920
First, to Mr. Prime Minister.

362
00:29:11,400 --> 00:29:15,280
(You must take responsibility for
putting our nation in this crisis.)

363
00:29:21,040 --> 00:29:22,440
You must resign!

364
00:29:42,520 --> 00:29:47,120
But we also do not condone violence
and public disturbance.

365
00:29:48,400 --> 00:29:53,040
We are talking directly to the protesters,
and calling for peaceful demonstrations.

366
00:29:53,800 --> 00:29:55,600
Because it is nothing to be proud of

367
00:29:55,840 --> 00:30:00,240
if we won this fight
on the ruins of our own nation!

368
00:31:05,680 --> 00:31:07,000
Watch out!

369
00:31:14,080 --> 00:31:20,160
May the Lord Warrior
be full and satisfied.

370
00:31:33,520 --> 00:31:35,240
There has been a disturbance at
MOVEMENTS AT STUDENT
ASSOCIATION’S GATHERING

371
00:31:35,240 --> 00:31:39,480
the Student Association’s gathering,

372
00:31:39,480 --> 00:31:43,400
when a group of outsiders threw
fake explosives among the students.

373
00:31:43,440 --> 00:31:45,360
We have nothing to do with it.

374
00:31:45,360 --> 00:31:46,720
We didn’t do anything.

375
00:31:46,920 --> 00:31:48,400
How could you say the protesters
DISTURBANCE AT
STUDENTS’ PROTEST

376
00:31:48,400 --> 00:31:51,760
have harmed those students
when the explosives were fake?

377
00:31:51,880 --> 00:31:54,480
This must be the work
of a third or even a fourth party.

378
00:31:54,520 --> 00:31:56,080
Then how would you explain
what’s wrong with them?

379
00:31:56,240 --> 00:31:57,400
I wouldn’t know.

380
00:31:57,600 --> 00:31:59,040
I believe that’s a question for the doctors.

381
00:32:48,440 --> 00:32:48,880
Pete.

382
00:32:49,280 --> 00:32:49,720
Pete!

383
00:32:49,760 --> 00:32:50,520
Hey! Pete!

384
00:32:51,280 --> 00:32:51,760
Hey!

385
00:32:52,320 --> 00:32:52,680
Pete.

386
00:32:53,840 --> 00:32:55,080
I’ll kill them!

387
00:32:55,360 --> 00:32:55,680
Who?

388
00:32:55,840 --> 00:32:57,280
Those assholes with the bombs!

389
00:32:57,280 --> 00:32:58,280
I’ll kill every one of them!

390
00:33:02,080 --> 00:33:04,840
Those people are just decoys.

391
00:33:05,680 --> 00:33:09,560
Your sister is like this because her life spirit
has been devoured by Qi Rong.

392
00:33:12,680 --> 00:33:13,440
Calm down.

393
00:33:14,480 --> 00:33:15,200
Trust me.

394
00:33:19,040 --> 00:33:19,680
Calm down.

395
00:33:31,720 --> 00:33:32,920
What’s going on?

396
00:33:57,480 --> 00:34:00,480
Is that… what I think it is?

397
00:34:08,800 --> 00:34:10,480
The mark of a sacrifice.

398
00:34:12,239 --> 00:34:17,639
Someone used these kids’ gathering
to sacrifice their life spirits to the demon.

399
00:34:20,280 --> 00:34:25,320
Anyone who was carrying this pin on them
didn’t stand a chance.

400
00:34:27,159 --> 00:34:28,280
A life spirit sacrifice?

401
00:34:29,320 --> 00:34:32,800
Life spirit is a crucial part
of the human soul.

402
00:34:33,679 --> 00:34:36,960
If your life spirit leaves your body,

403
00:34:39,040 --> 00:34:41,080
you are no better than a corpse.

404
00:34:41,880 --> 00:34:44,679
You’ll keep breathing,
but you’re no longer alive.

405
00:34:46,320 --> 00:34:51,560
Nothing is as powerful as an offering
to a demon than a life spirit.

406
00:34:52,480 --> 00:34:56,280
Two or three life spirits
would be bad enough.

407
00:34:56,560 --> 00:34:58,040
But someone just sacrificed
more than a hundred.

408
00:34:59,720 --> 00:35:04,200
I never thought I’d come across
someone so cruel.

409
00:35:12,720 --> 00:35:16,600
Most of Bao Cheng’s men
are now under arrest, ma’am.

410
00:35:19,800 --> 00:35:20,560
Who is this?

411
00:35:21,600 --> 00:35:22,240
Him?

412
00:35:23,000 --> 00:35:25,600
Our informer says he’s been
with Bao Cheng for many years.

413
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:28,720
They said he’s just a spiritual advisor.

414
00:35:47,560 --> 00:35:50,560
BETONG

415
00:35:56,600 --> 00:35:58,880
Once we seal Qi Rong away,

416
00:36:00,120 --> 00:36:01,600
my sister will be
back to normal, won’t she?

417
00:36:06,160 --> 00:36:06,680
Umm.

418
00:36:12,560 --> 00:36:13,800
When can we start?

419
00:36:17,080 --> 00:36:18,480
That depends on you.

420
00:36:20,080 --> 00:36:25,640
Once you can control the Six-Eared,
we’ll begin right away.

421
00:36:27,840 --> 00:36:29,680
I’ll admit you’re stronger now, Pete.

422
00:36:30,720 --> 00:36:32,560
But you still have one big weakness.

423
00:36:39,040 --> 00:36:40,640
It’s my anger, isn’t it?

424
00:36:43,480 --> 00:36:44,080
Yes.

425
00:36:45,640 --> 00:36:50,360
Anger will only undermine your strength.

426
00:36:51,160 --> 00:36:56,800
The more you accumulate it,
the more your life force depletes.

427
00:37:03,880 --> 00:37:06,240
I need to control my anger, don’t I?

428
00:37:09,520 --> 00:37:10,840
Haven’t you been doing that?

429
00:37:12,400 --> 00:37:13,120
And?

430
00:37:14,240 --> 00:37:15,080
Did it ever work?

431
00:37:24,760 --> 00:37:25,840
There’s a breeze right now.

432
00:37:26,760 --> 00:37:27,720
Can you feel it?

433
00:37:29,800 --> 00:37:30,360
Umm.

434
00:37:31,040 --> 00:37:32,440
Can you stop it from blowing?

435
00:37:34,680 --> 00:37:36,160
How the hell would I do that?

436
00:37:37,560 --> 00:37:38,160
That’s right.

437
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:39,840
You can’t.

438
00:37:40,680 --> 00:37:42,040
Because breezes are natural.

439
00:37:42,720 --> 00:37:46,560
They form, blow, and pass you by.

440
00:38:19,200 --> 00:38:22,000
Now do you notice the breeze has gone?

441
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:24,360
Do you still feel it?

442
00:38:27,080 --> 00:38:27,720
I don’t.

443
00:38:28,600 --> 00:38:29,280
You don’t.

444
00:38:30,440 --> 00:38:31,720
That’s because the wind
has blown through.

445
00:38:32,800 --> 00:38:36,560
The next breeze you feel will be
entirely new, not what you felt before.

446
00:38:38,040 --> 00:38:41,560
And that, too, will pass you by,
just like the one before.

447
00:38:42,840 --> 00:38:44,080
Just like all breezes do.

448
00:39:04,040 --> 00:39:04,800
Don’t forget, Pete.

449
00:39:06,320 --> 00:39:09,280
A breeze blows and blows through.

450
00:40:13,400 --> 00:40:14,400
Pete!

451
00:40:14,400 --> 00:40:15,480
Where the hell were you yesterday?

452
00:40:15,480 --> 00:40:16,280
Why did you skip training?

453
00:40:17,800 --> 00:40:19,000
Answer me!

454
00:40:23,400 --> 00:40:24,600
Are you angry?

455
00:40:26,000 --> 00:40:26,920
Go on!

456
00:40:27,360 --> 00:40:28,040
Do it!

457
00:40:28,240 --> 00:40:29,440
What are you waiting for?

458
00:40:29,960 --> 00:40:31,040
Maybe you don’t quite dare.

459
00:40:32,080 --> 00:40:32,800
Loser!

460
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:33,960
You’re a loser!

461
00:40:33,960 --> 00:40:35,400
You’re a freaking loser!

462
00:40:39,240 --> 00:40:40,840
Or what? You wanna kill me?

463
00:40:41,000 --> 00:40:41,840
Go on!

464
00:40:42,400 --> 00:40:43,160
Punch me!

465
00:40:43,280 --> 00:40:44,040
Do it!

466
00:40:44,520 --> 00:40:45,760
I said punch me!

467
00:40:46,560 --> 00:40:47,240
Punch me!

468
00:40:47,480 --> 00:40:48,080
(Don’t forget.)

469
00:40:49,360 --> 00:40:52,960
(A breeze blows and blows through.)

470
00:40:52,960 --> 00:40:54,000
Punch me!

471
00:40:54,040 --> 00:40:55,360
What are you waiting for?

472
00:40:55,360 --> 00:40:56,200
Punch me!

473
00:40:56,600 --> 00:40:57,520
Forget it, Coach.

474
00:41:00,960 --> 00:41:01,800
It’s gone now.

475
00:41:11,400 --> 00:41:12,800
How is his energy?

476
00:41:14,680 --> 00:41:15,680
It’s back in balance.

477
00:41:17,240 --> 00:41:19,600
…If I sense it correctly.

478
00:41:20,720 --> 00:41:22,160
Be more confident in yourself!

479
00:41:35,280 --> 00:41:35,880
Pete!

480
00:41:35,880 --> 00:41:37,240
Where the hell were you yesterday?

481
00:41:37,240 --> 00:41:37,960
Why did you skip training?v

482
00:41:39,800 --> 00:41:40,720
Answer me!

483
00:41:41,880 --> 00:41:45,200
Don’t you realize what kind of
expectations your parents had for you?

484
00:41:45,720 --> 00:41:47,040
Let me ask you honestly, Pete.

485
00:41:47,680 --> 00:41:48,760
Why were you born?

486
00:41:49,080 --> 00:41:50,000
Just to be a scumbag?

487
00:41:51,200 --> 00:41:52,640
A useless scumbag.

488
00:41:53,040 --> 00:41:54,040
Why were you even born?

489
00:41:54,960 --> 00:41:56,560
Why did it have to be your parents
who were dead?

490
00:41:56,960 --> 00:41:59,240
You deserve to die more than anyone.

491
00:41:59,360 --> 00:42:00,600
Why were you born, Pete?

492
00:42:00,600 --> 00:42:01,280
Why?

493
00:42:01,280 --> 00:42:01,880
Why?

494
00:42:02,000 --> 00:42:03,400
Why were you even born?

495
00:42:03,400 --> 00:42:04,280
This isn’t real!

496
00:42:09,000 --> 00:42:11,120
You didn’t say any of this to me, Coach.

497
00:42:13,320 --> 00:42:15,280
This is all just the voices in my head!

498
00:42:16,680 --> 00:42:17,240
You jerk!

499
00:42:53,960 --> 00:42:54,440
Shit!

500
00:44:02,800 --> 00:44:04,400
You wanna stay with me, huh?

501
00:44:06,000 --> 00:44:06,680
Alright.

502
00:44:07,440 --> 00:44:10,200
But I’m the boss around here, not you!

503
00:44:41,880 --> 00:44:43,280
I undid the seal.

504
00:44:44,520 --> 00:44:48,200
That thing behind your ear,
it’s just a regular tattoo now.

505
00:44:48,840 --> 00:44:50,640
It’s no longer a seal suppressing a demon.

506
00:44:53,520 --> 00:44:54,000
But…

507
00:44:55,400 --> 00:44:56,640
What will happen to me now?

508
00:44:59,320 --> 00:45:01,320
Do you still feel like yourself?

509
00:45:04,520 --> 00:45:05,480
Hell yeah.

510
00:45:06,240 --> 00:45:08,520
Then you have the demon under control.

511
00:45:59,280 --> 00:45:59,840
Niran.

512
00:46:00,400 --> 00:46:01,120
What’s wrong?

513
00:46:01,880 --> 00:46:03,520
You looked drained as hell ever since
we were done with the ritual.

514
00:46:05,680 --> 00:46:06,280
It’s nothing.

515
00:46:07,000 --> 00:46:10,720
The demon disturbed
my energy quite a bit.

516
00:46:11,600 --> 00:46:15,040
It’ll take some time for me
to get myself back in balance.

517
00:46:17,600 --> 00:46:18,120
Oh?

518
00:46:19,080 --> 00:46:20,240
Doesn’t that mean I did this?

519
00:46:21,200 --> 00:46:22,360
Oh, it’s not like that.

520
00:46:23,360 --> 00:46:25,240
This kind of thing happens all the time.

521
00:46:25,960 --> 00:46:28,840
I’m pretty much immune
after years of defeating yao,

522
00:46:30,040 --> 00:46:35,920
but there are still times
when I just can’t handle it.

523
00:46:37,760 --> 00:46:39,720
Is it like when I saw yao for the first time?

524
00:46:41,440 --> 00:46:43,480
Pretty much.

525
00:46:46,600 --> 00:46:46,960
Hey.

526
00:46:51,600 --> 00:46:52,160
What?

527
00:46:59,320 --> 00:46:59,680
Huh?

528
00:47:00,560 --> 00:47:02,560
I’ll do for you what you did for me.

529
00:47:12,600 --> 00:47:14,240
It’s my turn now.

530
00:47:16,840 --> 00:47:21,960
The evil forces that you’ve encountered, felt, and still touched by,

531
00:47:24,280 --> 00:47:25,480
transfer them to me.

532
00:47:29,040 --> 00:47:30,440
Just transfer them all to me.

533
00:47:56,240 --> 00:47:59,400
I don’t know if it works since I’m no Wu.

534
00:48:00,560 --> 00:48:02,640
I just don’t want you to carry it alone.

535
00:48:06,520 --> 00:48:07,320
Damn.

536
00:48:07,960 --> 00:48:09,280
Maybe it’s not working.

537
00:48:17,040 --> 00:48:21,520
